===Etymology===
Possibly related to {{cog|bo|སྡོམ|t=spider}}, which is likely related to {{cog|bo|སྡོམ|t=to bind; to tie}}, {{och-l|蔪|to entwine}} ({{zh-ref|Bodman, 1980}}; {{zh-ref|Coblin, 1986}}). The [[silkworm]], as the [[spider]], would thus be seen as a "binder; spinner". Compare the semantic development of {{ncog|en|spider}}, ultimately from {{ncog|gem-pro|*spinnaną||to spin}}.

These may be derived from {{der|zh|sit-pro|*tip ~ *tu(p/m)|t=to wrap up}}, whence also {{m|bo|གཏུམ|t=to wrap up}}, {{cog|my|ထုပ်|t=to wrap, bundle}}; other Chinese comparanda include {{och-l|縶|to rope, tether, bind}}{{,}} and {{och-l|纏|to bind}} (STEDT).

